:'''B'''{{note|Eaton}}: Eaton went so far as to write: "When botanists are so infatuated with wild speculation, as to tell us the mullein was introduced, they give our youngest pupils occasion to sneer at their teachers."<ref name="pennel">{{Cite book| last=Pennel| first=Francis Whittier| title=The Scrophulariaceae of eastern temperate North America| year=1935| publisher=George W. Carpenter Fund| location=Philadelphia| pages=pp.173-174| oclc=852625}}</ref>
